title: Men's Elite Eight live tracker: Highlights, updates on Duke vs. Alabama
description: Follow along as we track all the action in Saturday night's games.
author: ESPN Staff

title: Clayton's late flurry sends Florida into Final Four
description: Florida All-American guard Walter Clayton Jr. caught fire late, leading a comeback over Texas Tech that has the Gators in the Final Four.
author: Kyle Bonagura

title: 'It will be special' - Forest reach first FA Cup semi since 1991
description: Nottingham Forest's "incredible" season continues as they beat Brighton on penalties to reach the FA Cup semi-finals for the first time in 34 years.

title: GB win first world figure skating medal since 1984
description: Lilah Fear and Lewis Gibson win GB's first figure skating World Championship medal since Torvill and Dean in 1984 with ice dance bronze in Boston.

title: Warrington fight back against Leeds as Wakefield dominate Leigh
description: A Jake Thewlis try proved the difference as Warrington Wolves fought back for a 16-14 win against Leeds Rhinos in round six of Super League on a landmark night at the Halliwell Jones Stadium.

title: Mayer-Ryan reignite rivalry in rematch on Sky Sports: All you need to know
description: Mikaela Mayer and Sandy Ryan reignite their rivalry in a rematch, just a few months after a paint attack marred the build-up to their first world title fight.

title: Lady Vols basketball players reflect on March Madness run: 'We did something special'
description: Kim Caldwell and the Lady Vols stuck to their full-court press all game against Texas in the Sweet 16, showing the potential of the style of play.

title: Devils beat Wild, 5-2, behind Nico Hischier's hat trick
description: Nico Hischier scored three goals for his second hat trick of the season and the New Jersey Devils beat the Minnesota Wild 5-2 on Saturday.
